Search

Diagnostic Console Â» Search in Diagnostic Services

 

With this command you can find any string in the tree view of the available diagnostic services. The action activates the search mode, the search panel will open, focus will jump to edit field and search edit field is clear.

Enter the search string in the search panel. The first occurrence of the search string is marked. In the same time the properties of the service fount is displayed in the right window.

Press the <F3> key or the button in order to find the next occurrence of the entered phrase. On the other hand you can press the <Shift>+<F3> or button in order to find the previous occurrence of the current search phrase.

Pressing <ESC> or the toolbar button while performing a search deactivates the search mode and closes the search panel.

Note

  • The background of the edit field becomes red if the entered search phrase is not found at all.
  • The search functionality is case-insensitive.
  • The search functionality is support a basic set of wildcards (* and ?).
  • Pressing <Return> while performing a search accepts the current search result and the selected service is executed.
  • When the end of the search in the tree view of the available diagnostic services is reached, it is continued at the beginning.

Keyboard
